        <p>You can apply a superscript effect to text, where some text appears above the regular text (e.g., X<sup>2</sup>). Perhaps the easiest way to do this is to highlight the text, select the Home ribbon or Text Format toolbar, and click <img src="../../Images/superscript_btn1.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Analyzer,Products.Contributor">However, you can also change the properties of a different tag so that it appears as superscript text.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
